  "texts": [
    "ML models require a great amount of data, and the quality and the selection of the data greatly affects the quality of the output model.",
    "In thermal comfort modeling, data are even harder to come by as it uses intrusive methods that require occupants' input.",
    "Additionally, thermal comfort data are inherently class-imbalanced, which may result in illconditioned models.",
    "In building modeling, realistic data such as occupancy, temperature settings, and schedules are crucial, and without them, the outcomes of models may be inaccurate or have a high level of uncertainty.",
    "Furthermore, the realistic data required may be completely dependent on the application in which the data are needed."
  ],
